{"id":"spgr-jpp.10","title":"UpdateSpec handler returns CodeNotFound for all storage errors, including non-not-found failures","description":"File: internal/server/spec_handler.go, UpdateSpec method (line ~5587)

    spec, err := h.backend.UpdateSpec(ctx, msg.Slug, msg.Intent, msg.Stage, msg.Priority, msg.Complexity)
    if err != nil {
        return nil, connect.NewError(connect.CodeNotFound, err)
    }

Any storage error — database connection failure, Cypher query error, serialization problem — is reported to the client as CodeNotFound. This is incorrect and misleading: a transient database error should be CodeInternal, not CodeNotFound. The same pattern is present in DecisionHandler.UpdateDecision (internal/server/decision_handler.go, ~line 4893).

Suggested fix: Distinguish not-found errors (e.g., via a sentinel error or error unwrapping) from other storage errors and map them to CodeNotFound and CodeInternal respectively. A simple approach is to define a storage.ErrNotFound sentinel and check errors.Is.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"4678+seanb4t@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-03-01T00:38:08Z","created_by":"seanb4t","updated_at":"2026-03-01T00:38:08Z","external_ref":"https://github.com/seanb4t/specgraph/pull/4"}

{"id":"spgr-jpp.22","title":"readLine in init.go silently discards io errors, treating partial/failed reads as valid input","description":"File: cmd/specgraph/init.go, readLine function (lines 700-706)

    func readLine(r *bufio.Reader) string {
        line, err := r.ReadString('\n')
        if err != nil {
            return strings.TrimSpace(line) // return partial on EOF
        }
        return strings.TrimSpace(line)
    }

The comment says 'return partial on EOF' but the function also swallows any other io.Reader errors (e.g., broken pipe, device error) without distinguishing them from EOF. A broken-pipe or read error mid-input will return the partial content as if it were the user's intentional answer. This can silently accept an empty or partial backend/mode value, which then propagates into the written config file.

Suggested fix: Return (string, error) from readLine and handle non-EOF errors explicitly in runInit. Alternatively, check errors.Is(err, io.EOF) and return an error for any other read failure.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"4678+seanb4t@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-03-01T00:38:27Z","created_by":"seanb4t","updated_at":"2026-03-01T00:38:27Z","external_ref":"https://github.com/seanb4t/specgraph/pull/4"}

{"id":"spgr-jpp.16","title":"readLine returns same value in both branches — dead error branch","description":"In cmd/specgraph/init.go the readLine helper returns strings.TrimSpace(line) in both the error branch and the success branch. The two branches are identical, making the error check meaningless noise.

