      driveThreshold   = 20.0
      supportThreshold = 100.0
  )

Then the comparison reads: avg < driveThreshold — no cast needed.

Alternatively, compute total/len as integer division (total/len(messages)) and compare directly against int constants, avoiding float entirely. The current approach is correct but the cast is unnecessary given that untyped constants adapt to context.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"4678+seanb4t@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-03-04T02:16:09Z","created_by":"seanb4t","updated_at":"2026-03-04T02:16:09Z","external_ref":"https://github.com/seanb4t/specgraph/pull/8"}

{"id":"spgr-34l.19","title":"[types] Stage constants are untyped strings; AuthoringStage typed alias not used at authoring package boundary","description":"internal/authoring/stages.go defines stage constants as untyped string constants (not as AuthoringStage values):

